features.name: SOR_SNZ Belongs to the PdxS SNZ family

KdpA Part of the high-affinity ATP-driven potassium transport (or Kdp) system, which catalyzes the hydrolysis of ATP coupled with the electrogenic transport of potassium into the cytoplasm. This subunit binds and transports the potassium across the cytoplasmic membrane

E1-E2_ATPase,Hydrolase Part of the high-affinity ATP-driven potassium transport (or Kdp) system, which catalyzes the hydrolysis of ATP coupled with the electrogenic transport of potassium into the cytoplasm. This subunit is responsible for energy coupling to the transport system

KdpC Part of the high-affinity ATP-driven potassium transport (or Kdp) system, which catalyzes the hydrolysis of ATP coupled with the electrogenic transport of potassium into the cytoplasm. This subunit acts as a catalytic chaperone that increases the ATP- binding affinity of the ATP-hydrolyzing subunit KdpB by the formation of a transient KdpB KdpC ATP ternary complex
BBP2 Putative beta-barrel porin-2, OmpL-like. bbp2
Response_reg,Trans_reg_C COG0745 Response regulators consisting of a CheY-like receiver domain and a winged-helix DNA-binding domain
PIN Toxic component of a toxin-antitoxin (TA) module. An RNase
AAA_31 PFAM Cobyrinic acid a,c-diamide synthase
VirB3 Type IV secretory pathway, VirB3-like protein
CagE_TrbE_VirB TIGRFAM type IV secretion conjugal transfer ATPase, VirB4 family
BPD_transp_2 Branched-chain amino acid transport system / permease component
TrbL TrbL/VirB6 plasmid conjugal transfer protein
VirB8 protein secretion by the type IV secretion system

DUF4113,IMS,IMS_C,IMS_HHH Poorly processive, error-prone DNA polymerase involved in untargeted mutagenesis. Copies undamaged DNA at stalled replication forks, which arise in vivo from mismatched or misaligned primer ends. These misaligned primers can be extended by PolIV. Exhibits no 3'-5' exonuclease (proofreading) activity. May be involved in translesional synthesis, in conjunction with the beta clamp from PolIII
Peptidase_S24 Belongs to the peptidase S24 family

AAA_30,HHH_4,HHH_5,UvrD_C_2 DNA-dependent ATPase and ATP-dependent 5'-3' DNA helicase. Has no activity on blunt DNA or DNA with 3'-overhangs, requires at least 10 bases of 5'-ssDNA for helicase activity
